  "canonical_term": "Dragonfly Doji",
  "aliases": [],
  "school": "Price Action",
  "definition": "A candlestick pattern with a long lower wick and a small real body near the top of the range, signaling a potential bullish reversal when appearing after a downtrend.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "The candle has a small or nonexistent real body located at the top of its range.",
    "The lower wick is significantly longer than the body, with no or very short upper wick.",
    "Occurs after a downtrend."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "Signals a potential bullish reversal. Traders may enter long on the candle close, with a stop loss below the candle's low or below a nearby support level. Often used alongside other confirmation signals (e.g., free bars, failure tests) for higher probability trades.",
